wn","metadata":{"id":"CRaF2A_j_nC7"},"source":["### Your task"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"zM9w2aUvJ7KN"},"source":["1. Let's compute some stats!  What is the number of ratings in the training and test dataset? How many movies are in our dataset? You should **print** all the numbers."]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"id":"8XZaH16t_CIw"},"source":["# YOUR CODE HERE\n","print( \"Number of ratings: \", training.count() )\n","print( \"Number of ratings: \", test.count() )\n","print( \"Number of movies: \", items.count() )"],"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"wpsaYOqRxar2"},"source":["2. Using the training set, train a model with the Alternating Least Squares method available in the Spark MLlib: [https://spark.apache.org/docs/latest/ml-collaborative-filtering.html](https://spark.apache.org/docs/latest/ml-collaborative-filtering.html)<br>Use **seed** when initializing ALS for consistent result."]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"id":"Oitav_xhQD9w"},"source":["# YOUR CODE HERE\n","from pyspark.ml.evaluation import RegressionEvaluator\n","from pyspark.ml.recommendation import ALS\n","from pyspark.sql import Row\n","\n","# Build the recommendation model using ALS on the training data\n","# Note we set cold start strategy to 'drop' to ensure we don't get NaN evaluation metrics\n","# maxIter is the maximum number of iterations to run (defaults to 10).\n","# regParam specifies the regularization parameter in ALS (defaults to 1.0).\n","# seed = consistent result\n","\n","als = ALS(maxIter=10, regParam=0.1, userCol=\"user_id\", itemCol=\"item_id\", ratingCol=\"rating\",\n","          coldStartStrategy=\"drop\", seed = 20211116)\n","model = als.fit(training)\n"],"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"TtR1xRvonxiO"},"source":["3. Now compute the RMSE on the test dataset. If RMSE is over **0.95**, go back to the previous step and try again with different parameters.\n"]},{"cell_typ